-------> WELCOME (5min)

Welcome to our inaugural fellowship service at Be The Church 624

My name is Nick and I have the honour of leading this ministry and this weekly fellowship service held every Thursday starting at 8pm ET

My wife and I have a strong desire to be in community with fellow Christians who are also seeking to meet the standard of excellence set by Jesus

We've struggled to find Christian fellowship locally so we decided to build this ministry as a way to grow a digital fellowship of comitted believers who want to pray, study scripture and discuss important topics together

I feel strongly that striving to understand the word of God and live righteously in a world of sin is best achieved in fellowship with other believers

From that belief, this fellowship service is our way of building a global community that offers strength in numbers and a means of perseverance to maintain faith to the end

These weekly services will be posted publicly as a podcast. If you get value from them, you can donate to support BTC264

If you want to join as a fellow, you can email us at BeTheChurch624@protonmail.com or send us a DM on nostr which is a social media protocol that isnt owned or controlled by a company and integrates bitcoin micro payments

Our family attends a church based in Atlanda called 2819, led by pastor Phillip Anthony Mitchell

Inspired by their approach of slowly moving through scripture, we are beginning our exploration of the Bible today with the gospel according to Matthew

We will not be rushing and we don't have a set schedule other than time allotted every week to reading every verse line by line until we finish Matthew and move on to the next book

We aren't reading scripture for the sake of just reading it

Our objeictive is to study the word deeply to truly understand what is being said and then discussing how we as Christians can apply these lessons to live up to the very clear and very high bar set for us by Jesus


We want this fellowship service to be a high signal, valuable offering which means they will be highly structured and the structure will evolve over time based on feeback from our fellows and listeners

Todays session will go like this:
- 5 minute welcome
- 2 minute opening prayer
- 20 minutes of scripture
- 10 minute discussion on behaviour, today we're talking about the specific behaviour of reading the bible
- 10 minute discussion on stewardship, today we're talking about sinful currency
- 2min closing prayer
- 10 min stories/discussion (optional)

In future we will have a 30 minute cyber social after the service and worship music leading up to our 8pm start




